x;">One faithful Wall Street eminence, a lusty contrarian, wrote to me on M=
onday that his
=E2=80=9Cdecades=E2=80=9D of market experience has led him to the conclusio=
n that =E2=80=9Cstocks have their sharpest drops from their highest peaks w=
hen all see only upside.=E2=80=9D I=E2=80=99d say we experienced a healthy =
dose of reality on Monday. I think we have a few more doses to take before =
we=E2=80=99re done here, even if in the longer run, owning stocks=E2=80=94a=
t least over the past 45 years or so=E2=80=94has proved to be a major wealt=
h generator.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=
=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">As the
dust settles after Monday=E2=80=99s selloff, I=E2=80=99ve noticed some cool=
er, perhaps wiser, heads prevailing. BNP Paribas Securities=E2=80=99 chief =
U.S. economist, <strong>James Egelhof</strong>, wrote that the DeepSeek bre=
akthrough will be good news in the long run. =E2=80=9CWe think cheaper A.I.=
 means more A.I., more quickly,=E2=80=9D he wrote. =E2=80=9CThis should mea=
n a greater and more rapid productivity boom as the A.I. rollout snowballs.=
 We are not concerned about recession risks directly ensuing from, for exam=
ple, reduced investment
in data centers, and we think software investment might rise to offset decl=
ines in data center investment.=E2=80=9D</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bot=
tom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Then there=E2=
=80=99s <strong>Pat Gelsinger</strong>, the former C.E.O. of Intel, who kno=
ws a thing or two about chips and falling off a high perch. (Intel, which h=
as had its lunch almost completely eaten by Nvidia, is often mentioned as a=
 takeover candidate these days.) =E2=80=9CWisdom is learning the lessons we
thought we already knew,=E2=80=9D he <a href=3D"https://email.puck.news/e/c=
/eyJlbWFpbF9pZCI6ImRnVDJ4Z1lEQUt2UktxclJLZ0dVdEowc3FKVmhyMU1aZVFubEVxWT0iLC=
JocmVmIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly94LmNvbS9QR2Vsc2luZ2VyL3N0YXR1cy8xODgzODk2ODM3NDI3NTg1M=
DM1P3V0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1EcnkrUG93ZGVyKy0rU1VCU0NSSUJFUlMrJTI4MSUyRjI5JTJGMjUl=
MjlcdTAwMjZ1dG1fY29udGVudD1EcnkrUG93ZGVyKy0rU1VCU0NSSUJFUlMrJTI4MSUyRjI5JTJ=
GMjUlMjlcdTAwMjZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsX2FjdGlvblx1MDAyNnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9Y3VzdG=
9tZXIuaW9cdTAwMjZ1dG1fdGVybT1mNmM2MDYxN2RhNDJhYmQxMmEiLCJpbnRlcm5hbCI6ImY2Y=
zYwNjE3ZGE0MmFiZDEyYSIsImxpbmtfaWQiOjIwNjQ2MzB9/84b7b4d0a0e5acb1fd2d1d444de=
887243c1684a7e8c297d550e4f01cdff47e06" style=3D"text-decoration:underline;c=
olor:#d40000;">posted</a> on X on Monday, saying DeepSeek offers three less=
ons. First, computing =E2=80=9Cobeys the gas law=E2=80=94[m]aking it dramat=
ically cheaper will expand the market for it. The markets are getting it wr=
ong, this will make A.I. much more broadly deployed.=E2=80=9D Second, =E2=
=80=9C[e]ngineering is about constraints. The Chinese engineers had limited=
 resources and had to find
creative solutions.=E2=80=9D And, finally, =E2=80=9COpen Wins.=E2=80=9D Dee=
pSeek, Gelsinger said, will help =E2=80=9Creset the increasingly closed wor=
ld of foundational A.I. model work.=E2=80=9D He signed off, =E2=80=9CThank =
you DeepSeek team.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;"><br/>Tom =
Lee, despite being a perennial bull, has been pretty much right to be exube=
rant for the 34 years or so he=E2=80=99s been studying and commenting on th=
e stock market. I think we=E2=80=99re still in need of a major correction, =
myself=E2=80=94especially in a number of these crazy meme
stocks, such as Tesla and MicroStrategy, among <em>many</em> others, which =
have gotten far out over their skis for no good reason. But Lee said someth=
ing else on CNBC that stuck with me. =E2=80=9CMarkets just generally do <em=
>fire</em>, <em>ready</em>, <em>aim</em>,=E2=80=9D he remarked, quoting the=
 old Wall Street truism. That=E2=80=99s what happened on Monday.</p></div>
